      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong> and <strong>ground coriander</strong> to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add your <strong>salmon fillet[s]</strong> and press them firmly into the spice mix until evenly coated all over</p>",
